Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of parallelization in convex optimization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of adaptivity as an information theoretic measure suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The study of optimization algorithms and their efficiency suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. The focus on lower bounds and limitations suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the use of black-box oracle access suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.OH (Other Computer Science) sub-category.
